            <line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/>
          </svg>
          FERS Supplement Earnings Test
        </h3>
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-body); color: #64748b; line-height: 1.6;">If you receive the FERS supplement and work after retirement, your supplement is reduced $1 for every $2 you earn over $23,400 (2025 limit). This makes post-retirement employment planning crucial for supplement recipients. The test only applies to earned income — investment income, TSP withdrawals, and your FERS annuity don't count.</p>
      </div>
      
      <p class="fed-ed-ss-body">The supplement automatically ends when you turn 62, regardless of whether you claim Social Security. This creates a potential income cliff that must be planned for — your supplement might stop, but you may choose to delay actual Social Security for higher benefits later.</p>
